1
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:38,733
<i> I'll marry you.</i>

2
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:41,067
<i>I'll make sure that we get
married as soon as possible.</i>

3
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,300
<i> What happened to you?</i>

4
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:44,000
<i> I need to finish my contract,</i>

5
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,800
<i>so that Andrea can get
the operation.</i>

6
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>I talked to our supervisor
earlier.</i>

7
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> He'll lend you some money.</i>

8
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,433
<i>Once I get the money I need,
I'll return to the Philippines.</i>

9
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>Are you going to run away
from the supervisor?</i>

10
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:54,033
<i>Sign the contract,
get the money,</i>

11
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:55,533
<i> and send it to Felma.</i>

12
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,400
<i>I really won't be able
to get away from Hazel.</i>

13
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:58,633
<i> I have to marry her.</i>

14
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:01,067
<i>Under the laws of the
Republic of the Philippines,</i>

15
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,933
<i> I ask you, Manuel Cruz,</i>

16
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:05,933
<i>to be united in marriage
to Hazel Capistrano.</i>

17
00:01:06,667 --> 00:01:08,000
<i> I do.</i>

18
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:10,733
<i>- Manuel?
- That's a woman's voice.</i>

19
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:12,267
<i> Are you with a woman?</i>

20
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,067
<i>I have to go.
I'll just call you again.</i>

21
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,233
<i> Bye. Be safe, Love.</i>

22
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:17,867
<i> You too.</i>

23
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,267
<i> Hello?</i>

24
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:21,267
<i>Do you still call that woman
"Love"?</i>

25
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,600
Why are you getting mad?

26
00:01:25,267 --> 00:01:27,167
I just talked to Felma.

27
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:29,433
You know our daughter's
condition.

28
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,667
I just wanted to know
if she's doing okay.

29
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,767
So, is she okay now?

30
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:35,733
I hope.

31
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:37,367
Good.

32
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,400
That means you can now stop
communicating with them.

33
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:42,467
Why?

34
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,900
They're still my family.

35
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:45,900
I'm your family now, Manuel.

36
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,567
Our baby and I.

37
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:49,733
And as your wife,

38
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:52,133
I have the right to prohibit you
from talking to Felma.

39
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:53,467
Do you understand?

40
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:56,967
You're cutting my connection
with them?

41
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,533
I won't let that happen!

42
00:01:58,667 --> 00:01:59,667
Why?

43
00:02:01,567 --> 00:02:05,833
Just admit that you don't want
to break up with Felma.

44
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:12,467
See?

45
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:14,867
You're cheating on me.

46
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:16,667
You're cheating on me

47
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,833
on our first night
as a married couple.

48
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:20,500
What are you talking about,
Hazel?

49
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,767
You know from the beginning
that it's Felma I love.

50
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:26,967
She and our children.

51
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:31,133
Don't act as if
I'm cheating on you.

52
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:33,333
Hazel, I married you,

53
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:35,633
but that doesn't mean
I need to love you!

54
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:09,200
So what will you do?

55
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,300
Will you stop calling
your family?

56
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,533
I can't do that.

57
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:16,933
How will I know
what's happening to them?

58
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,500
But I'm worried about Felma.

59
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,133
She might start noticing it.

60
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:23,900
She won't.

61
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,000
You have a valid excuse.

62
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:29,300
I know. But I have to lie
every time I call.

63
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:30,600
I always need to make an alibi.

64
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,233
It's such a heavy feeling, Bro.

65
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,933
Sometimes, I think it's better
not to call them.

66
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:39,967
It's only like that
at first, man.

67
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:41,167
You'll eventually
get used to it.

68
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,233
Look at me.

69
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,733
Paz doesn't catch on to me.

70
00:03:44,867 --> 00:03:46,767
I'm able to cheat
without Paz noticing.

71
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:47,400
See?

72
00:03:49,267 --> 00:03:51,900
I didn't tell them about Hazel.

73
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:54,167
I don't want them to get hurt.

74
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:59,200
But I can't stand lying to them.

75
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:04,267
What if I tell them the truth?

76
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,833
Are you crazy?

77
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:09,100
Do you want your wife
to break down in despair?

78
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,000
I forgot she's not your wife
anymore.

79
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,433
What about your kids?

80
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:16,033
Do you want them to hate you?

81
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:20,433
Remember, Andrea has just
undergone surgery.

82
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:21,967
She might get sick again.

83
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:22,733
I'm just warning you.

84
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,333
You're so strict
with your husband.

85
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,000
Why not?

86
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:33,467
He's mine now.

87
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:36,333
I have all the right
to protect what's mine.

88
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,767
Well, I'm also like that
with my husband.

89
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:41,933
I would fight
for the man I love.

90
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:45,333
But, Friend,

91
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:48,633
you don't really love Manuel,
right?

92
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,233
No.

93
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,933
Not really.

94
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:56,500
I'm just doing this for my baby.

95
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:00,400
But if I fall in love
with Manuel...

96
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:04,167
there's nothing wrong
with that, right?

97
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,400
Especially since
he's my husband now.

98
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:10,400
Whatever! Let's go.

99
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:16,833
Thank you.

100
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,367
Friend.

101
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:22,100
Here is Andrea's bill.

102
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,533
Do you have money to pay for it?

103
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,867
Manuel sent me money
just the other day.

104
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:38,900
I want to thank him.

105
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:40,467
But he's not calling.

106
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:45,767
I tried to call him
but I couldn't reach him.

107
00:05:46,433 --> 00:05:47,500
Let him be.

108
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:48,767
He's busy for sure.

109
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,300
He's probably working hard

110
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:54,033
to pay off his debt
to his supervisor.

111
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,400
Friend...

112
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:01,900
I miss my husband.

113
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:07,667
That's just how life is
for the wife of an OFW.

114
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:11,200
I also tell my husband
the same thing.

115
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:12,900
He keeps on working

116
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:15,733
from time to time,
he should try to enjoy himself.

117
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:18,033
By the way, Friend.

118
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:20,133
He sent me this the other day.

119
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:21,300
Wait.

120
00:06:22,733 --> 00:06:24,833
Picture from Saudi Arabia.

121
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,167
Here, look.

122
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:28,800
He finally had time for himself.

123
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:30,100
They went to the park.

124
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:31,200
It's beautiful, isn't it?

125
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,333
Yes.

126
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:36,167
That's where the OFWs go
during their day off.

127
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:37,833
There.

128
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:42,967
That's the famous store
in Saudi Arabia.

129
00:06:43,133 --> 00:06:44,600
That's where
they buy their gifts.

130
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:47,067
The ones he puts
in the balikbayan box.

131
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,533
That's where he buys those.

132
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:53,767
That's a party.

133
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:54,900
- Birthday party of...
- Birthday?

134
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:56,600
one of their colleagues.

135
00:06:56,733 --> 00:06:59,933
There, he and Manuel
managed to have some fun, right?

136
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,500
Who is this?

137
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:07,300
Wait, wait, wait.

138
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:09,433
Someone seems to be flirting
with someone else's husband.

139
00:07:09,567 --> 00:07:14,100
I'll pull all her hair out
if she did that to Abel.

140
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:29,633
Who is the woman
in the picture you were with?

141
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:32,533
What picture?

142
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:34,733
The picture that was taken
at your friend's birthday party.

143
00:07:34,867 --> 00:07:36,833
Abel was there, too.

144
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:39,133
The woman was holding on to you.

145
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:40,367
<i> Is that Hazel?</i>

146
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:43,467
<i>- Saudi!
- Let's take a picture!</i>

147
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,500
<i> Picture!</i>

148
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:46,033
<i> Say cheese!</i>

149
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:48,067
<i> Cheese!</i>

150
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,767
I have something to tell you,
Love.

151
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,200
Mom?

152
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:59,600
- Dear.
- Is that dad?

153
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:04,433
Can I talk to him?

154
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:06,733
Love.

155
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:09,000
Andrea wants to talk to you.

156
00:08:14,667 --> 00:08:15,967
Hello, Dad.

157
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:17,933
Hello, Andeng, my dear.

158
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:20,233
How are you?

159
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:21,867
I'm doing okay now.

160
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:23,767
But...

161
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:28,233
the wound in my chest
hasn't healed yet.

162
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:32,400
And the doctor said...

163
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:38,900
I'm not allowed
to laugh and cough yet.

164
00:08:39,033 --> 00:08:43,100
So it won't hurt.

165
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:46,367
Yes, so don't watch
funny videos yet.

166
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:49,267
-The grocery store's so crowded.
-Super.

167
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,700
We didn't get to go home
right away.

168
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,367
I know, right?

169
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,567
Who is he talking to?

170
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:01,533
Who else? It's his ex.

171
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,267
I thought you forbade him
from talking to them.

172
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:18,067
There's only one way
for that woman

173
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,367
to leave my husband alone.

174
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:23,333
I'll put her
where she should belong.

175
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:35,033
Miss Felma, you have a letter

176
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:36,700
- from Mr. Manuel!
- Yes, for a while.

177
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:41,800
Too bad, the kids already left
for school.

178
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:43,733
They've been waiting for this
for so long.

179
00:09:43,867 --> 00:09:45,533
- I just need you to sign it.
- Thank you.

180
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:47,100
Okay.

181
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:48,333
I just need to sign it.

182
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:50,133
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

183
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,167
Hello, Love?

184
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:04,533
Stop calling my husband love.

185
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:12,800
What do you mean by "husband"?

186
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,633
Yes.

187
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:16,133
Manuel is already my husband.

188
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,933
What do you mean by saying
Manuel is your husband?

189
00:10:31,067 --> 00:10:31,967
Who are you?

190
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,433
<i> You know me.</i>

191
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:35,300
We talked once.

192
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:39,200
I even helped my husband
get money for your child.

193
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:41,900
Are you Hazel?

194
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,767
Oh, yes!

195
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,967
Hazel Capistrano.

196
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,433
And may I add?

197
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:48,400
Cruz.

198
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,133
Because I'm now
Mrs. Manuel Cruz.

199
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:52,767
Manuel and I
are already married.

200
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:53,967
That's not true.

201
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:56,667
That's impossible.

202
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,500
You're just kidding.

203
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:00,433
I don't believe you!

204
00:11:00,567 --> 00:11:02,100
Let me talk to my husband!

205
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:03,267
Where's Manuel?

206
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,200
I told you to stop calling
my husband your husband!

207
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,533
Because I'm now Manuel's wife!

208
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:07,600
Manuel!

209
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,800
Manuel, talk to me!

210
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:12,067
No matter what you say or do...

211
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,900
Even if you scream,
there's nothing you can do.

212
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:15,933
Hazel, who are you talking to?

213
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:17,933
You know who I'm talking to?

214
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:19,067
Your ex.

215
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,667
Oh, here he is.

216
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,067
Talk to Manuel.

217
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,333
Did you call Felma?

218
00:11:23,467 --> 00:11:24,533
And why not?

219
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:25,767
She must know the truth!

220
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:26,967
So that she knows her place!

221
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,333
Tell her we're married!

222
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:30,600
-Tell her we're married, Manuel!
-Hello, Love?

223
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,533
Love? Why are you still
calling her love?

224
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:33,900
<i> Can you shut up?</i>

225
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:37,000
- Felma.
- Manuel, is that woman

226
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,400
telling the truth?

227
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,333
Is she your wife?

228
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,133
Felma, wait. Let me explain.

229
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,600
Answer my question!

230
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:46,800
Is it true?

231
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:49,033
Felma, you don't understand.

232
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:50,400
Is it true?

233
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:51,633
She just trapped me
into marriage.

234
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:52,833
How dare you! What do you mean
I trapped you?

235
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:54,300
- He wanted to marry me!
- Will you stop?

236
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,833
Let me talk to my wife!

237
00:11:55,967 --> 00:11:57,467
Wife? I'm your wife!

238
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,900
- Hey!
- Hello, Felma?

239
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:00,400
I said stop!

240
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:01,700
Manuel!

241
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:03,333
Manuel! Hey!

242
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,100
<i> Manuel, open the door!</i>

243
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:07,033
Hello, Love?

244
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:10,433
Stop calling me love!

245
00:12:12,467 --> 00:12:14,367
<i> So she's telling the truth.</i>

246
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,233
She's already your wife.

247
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,233
You're married.

248
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,600
<i> You're already married.</i>

249
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:28,667
Felma, I was forced to do that.

250
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:29,967
Forced?

251
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,467
Felma, something happened.

252
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,167
- I didn't mean it to happen.
<i> - But still,</i>

253
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,167
<i>something happened
between the two of you!</i>

254
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:45,100
Since when, Manuel?

255
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:47,833
How long have you been
cheating on me?

256
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,800
Felma, I'm not cheating on you.
It only happened once.

257
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:53,267
It's still cheating!

258
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,200
That's still infidelity!

259
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:57,633
Manuel!

260
00:12:58,633 --> 00:12:59,767
Manuel, open the door!

261
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:02,300
And you even married her.

262
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,467
Why?

263
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,367
<i> Why did you marry her?</i>

264
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,467
Open it!

265
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,067
It's complicated, Love.

266
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,800
There's a law
here in Saudi Arabia

267
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:13,100
that's why I was forced
to marry her.

268
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,700
<i> What law is that?</i>

269
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,233
Tell me what it is.

270
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:20,733
Explain to me.

271
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,600
-Hazel!
-I didn't force him to marry me!

272
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:23,867
He wanted it!

273
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:24,867
- Hazel!
- Did you hear that?

274
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,033
Because I'm pregnant!

275
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:28,100
- He got me pregnant!
- Hazel, wait!

276
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:29,533
Let me explain, Felma!

277
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:30,767
Hear me out.

278
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:32,233
You got her pregnant?

279
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,167
Why?

280
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:37,933
That means it didn't only
happen once.

281
00:13:38,733 --> 00:13:40,133
You're probably having an affair
with her!

282
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:41,867
No!

283
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,133
<i> Liar!</i>

284
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:45,267
You're a liar, Manuel!

285
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,600
<i> She's pregnant.</i>

286
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:48,000
<i>You're going to have a child
with her.</i>

287
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,567
We're struggling here

288
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,700
while you're having
an affair there?

289
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:53,367
- Hazel!
- Hello!

290
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,633
So now that you know,

291
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,533
I hope you're going
to leave my husband alone!

292
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:58,867
- You'll stop talking to him!
- Hazel!

293
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,400
Don't ever call him again!
Do you understand?

294
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:03,600
Manuel?

295
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:06,400
Manuel!

296
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,633
How dare you!
You're so shameless!

297
00:15:16,767 --> 00:15:17,733
You're the shameless one!

298
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:19,533
You hurt my wife!

299
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:27,900
If I ever hear you call
that woman your wife again,

300
00:15:28,033 --> 00:15:29,533
you won't get away
with just that!

301
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:31,333
Stop threatening me.

302
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:33,833
My point is...

303
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,667
you shouldn't have called Felma.

304
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:37,567
You should've waited for me
to tell her!

305
00:15:38,167 --> 00:15:38,767
When?

306
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:41,533
When?

307
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:44,700
When will you tell her?

308
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:47,533
See?

309
00:15:49,233 --> 00:15:51,133
You're not planning to tell her.

310
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:55,433
That's why that woman
has the nerve to call you

311
00:15:55,567 --> 00:15:56,900
because she thinks

312
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:59,500
you still want to keep
your relationship going!

313
00:15:59,633 --> 00:16:00,867
It's not like that.

314
00:16:01,967 --> 00:16:02,933
But we have children.

315
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:05,500
- They're my family, too.
- I am your family now!

316
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:10,233
I'm your wife now.

317
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:14,000
And my baby and I
are now your family.

318
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:16,100
We're your legal family.

319
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:19,700
You should focus on us now,
not on them.

320
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:21,967
How often should
I tell you that?

321
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,367
Don't you get it?

322
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,400
You're the one
who can't understand!

323
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:29,900
Manuel!

324
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,267
Manuel, where are you going?

325
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,167
Manuel!

326
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:04,300
I think I already know
why you asked me to come.

327
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:07,833
Friend...

328
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,833
Manuel...

329
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,933
is already married
to that Hazel.

330
00:17:25,567 --> 00:17:26,800
You already know?

331
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:34,267
If I hadn't forced Abel
to admit it,

332
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:37,933
he would've never told me
the truth.

333
00:17:38,067 --> 00:17:41,667
That there's actually
a flirtatious and wild woman

334
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,400
over there in Saudi Arabia!

335
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:45,967
There are many men
in Saudi Arabia!

336
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:49,133
Some of them are single,
but what did she do?

337
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,867
She took your husband!

338
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,100
- Gosh!
- He's no longer my husband.

339
00:17:56,567 --> 00:17:58,367
He was taken away from us.

340
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,933
And that playboy let himself
be taken away.

341
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:03,400
So? Aren't we going
to do anything?

342
00:18:03,533 --> 00:18:07,100
Friend? Oh, no, no, no!
That can't be!

343
00:18:07,233 --> 00:18:08,367
He's already married.

344
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:11,900
There's nothing
I can do about it.

345
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,867
Really? There's nothing
you can do?

346
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,067
Fine. Well, there's something
I can do.

347
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,167
- I'll call him. Hold on.
- Friend, don't.

348
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,267
- No, don't stop me!
- Friend, don't.

349
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,733
This can't be!

350
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,067
Area code...

351
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,500
Wait.

352
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:27,433
<i>The subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

353
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:29,933
What does this mean?

354
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,333
Did he turn the phone off?

355
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,200
Goodness!

356
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:43,933
Hello, Ling?

357
00:18:44,067 --> 00:18:46,133
<i> Stop calling me Ling!</i>

358
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:50,667
Where's your playboy friend
and his promiscuous mistress?

359
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,933
Ling, don't be mad at me.

360
00:18:53,067 --> 00:18:54,700
I didn't do anything wrong.

361
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:56,400
Oh, really?

362
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:58,567
You're not doing anything wrong?

363
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,500
<i> Abelardo Sebastian,</i>

364
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:03,600
<i>the moment I learn
that you have a mistress,</i>

365
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:06,100
I will cut that off!

366
00:19:06,867 --> 00:19:08,167
Bro, can I borrow your phone?

367
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:10,833
Who's that? Is that Manuel?

368
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:28,267
Paz wants to talk to you.

369
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:34,333
- Hello?
<i> - Manuel!</i>

370
00:19:35,267 --> 00:19:36,167
How dare you!

371
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,233
Felma has made sacrifices
for you!

372
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:40,833
You, animal!

373
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:42,133
And this is how you're going
to repay her?

374
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:43,300
You're so shameless!

375
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:44,667
Is she with you?

376
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:45,900
Nag him!

377
00:20:03,167 --> 00:20:04,433
Manuel?

378
00:20:04,567 --> 00:20:05,733
Hello, Felma.

379
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,200
How could you do this to me?

380
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,100
<i>Felma, wait.
Please hear me out.</i>

381
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:13,033
I didn't mean it to happen.

382
00:20:13,167 --> 00:20:14,233
I never wanted that to happen.

383
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:15,733
And it only happened once.

384
00:20:15,867 --> 00:20:16,933
We were drunk.

385
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:20,367
- It was Alice's birthday.
- You got her pregnant.

386
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:23,933
Felma, I never expected it
to happen.

387
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:25,767
You married her.

388
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:30,733
Felma, there's a law here
in Saudi Arabia...

389
00:20:30,867 --> 00:20:34,333
if you sleep with someone
you're not married to,

390
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:36,033
you can go to jail.

391
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:39,767
Hazel would have me jailed
if I didn't marry her.

392
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:41,467
You should've gone to jail!

393
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:45,100
Both of you should've been
thrown in jail!

394
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:48,000
You should've suffered
for what you did to me!

395
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:50,100
<i>Felma, if I've gone to jail,
how could I go to work?</i>

396
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,867
How could I get money
for Andrea's operation?

397
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:55,767
If you only know my sacrifice!

398
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,333
<i> Sacrifice?</i>

399
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,300
Are you really going
to tell me that?

400
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:02,700
Your sacrifice?

401
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:05,667
You cheated on me!

402
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,867
<i>You fooled me and your children!</i>

403
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,267
You should've thought about it

404
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,433
before you got wasted
with your woman!

405
00:21:13,567 --> 00:21:15,633
Felma, she's not my mistress.

406
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:19,000
Right...

407
00:21:20,467 --> 00:21:21,967
She's your wife now.

408
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:24,633
Me?

409
00:21:24,767 --> 00:21:26,267
What am I to you now?

410
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:27,067
A mistress?

411
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:29,967
Felma, listen carefully.

412
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,500
No matter what happens,
I love you so much.

413
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:34,100
You're the only woman
in my life.

414
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:37,367
You told me that before.

415
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:41,367
That you'd come back
and marry me.

416
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,133
Now?

417
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:44,867
How is that going to happen?

418
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:48,733
Felma, please.
Hazel and I are just married.

419
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:51,633
But you're still the one I love.

420
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:55,833
If you love me...

421
00:21:56,933 --> 00:22:00,033
you wouldn't hurt me
like this.

422
00:22:00,167 --> 00:22:01,633
Felma...

423
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:03,233
Listen to me. I'll find a way.

424
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:04,833
I'll fix this.

425
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,600
How can you fix this?

426
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:10,333
Felma, please.
Don't give up on me.

427
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:12,300
I'm begging you.
I love you so much.

428
00:22:12,433 --> 00:22:13,633
You know that.

429
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,733
Felma.

430
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:19,733
That's enough, Manuel.

431
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:21,033
Enough.

432
00:22:21,567 --> 00:22:23,167
Let's stop this.

433
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,667
Let's put an end to this.

434
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:28,333
No, Felma.

435
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:31,733
Felma, hello?

436
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:35,833
Felma?

437
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:37,533
Hello!

438
00:22:38,533 --> 00:22:39,700
<i> Felma!</i>

439
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:07,933
It hurts so much!

440
00:23:10,533 --> 00:23:13,133
It hurts!

441
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:43,333
Gosh!

442
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:45,533
This is definitely the fault
of that promiscuous woman!

443
00:23:45,667 --> 00:23:49,300
You saw how she touched
your husband, right?

444
00:23:49,433 --> 00:23:50,500
She's unbelievable!

445
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:54,633
If only the ticket to
Saudi Arabia wasn't expensive,

446
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,033
I would've attacked that witch.

447
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,700
Is this really happening? Sis?

448
00:24:05,067 --> 00:24:06,733
It feels like just
the other day...

449
00:24:06,867 --> 00:24:08,533
we were so happy.

450
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,567
Andrea had surgery.

451
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,533
Now, she's doing better.

452
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:16,433
Then we even talked about...

453
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:18,900
Manuel coming home.

454
00:24:27,533 --> 00:24:28,800
So, that's why...

455
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:32,300
So that's the reason
he doesn't answer.

456
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:36,567
He doesn't call me often
anymore.

457
00:24:38,233 --> 00:24:42,400
Because he's already busy
with his new family.

458
00:24:47,567 --> 00:24:49,867
How will you tell the kids
about it?

459
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:04,167
The kids shouldn't know.

460
00:25:08,667 --> 00:25:10,300
I don't want to hurt them.

461
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:23,467
Jopet has new shoes.
He's bragging about it.

462
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,433
I'll ask my dad to buy me
the same shoes.

463
00:25:25,567 --> 00:25:27,067
He'll bring it
when he gets home.

464
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,367
How will he get home?

465
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:30,233
You no longer have a father.

466
00:25:30,367 --> 00:25:31,567
What do you mean nothing?

467
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,600
He already has another kid
in Saudi Arabia.

468
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:34,667
That's it.

469
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:36,633
I need to talk to Felma, Bro.

470
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:37,867
She might not answer your call.

471
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,367
Let her cool down.

472
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:41,400
Bro, I hurt her.

473
00:25:41,533 --> 00:25:44,033
How will I explain it
to the kids?

474
00:25:44,167 --> 00:25:45,267
They already know.

475
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,633
How?

476
00:25:46,767 --> 00:25:48,833
Text me if you need anything.

477
00:25:48,967 --> 00:25:50,533
What's going on?

478
00:25:50,667 --> 00:25:51,533
Jeff!

479
00:25:51,667 --> 00:25:52,767
What happened?

480
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:54,900
Mom, is it true?

481
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:57,000
What is?

482
00:25:57,133 --> 00:25:58,667
Has dad already had another kid?

483
00:26:02,167 --> 00:26:03,567
Does he have a new family?
